üåü SoraEase makes it easier for Sora developers to develop Sora AI üí™

Signed-off-by: kubbot <3293172751ysy@gmail.com>

feat: Improve logging and fix threading issues

This commit includes several changes to improve the JVM's logging and threading capabilities.

- **Improved verbose logging:** The verbose log output now includes the class and method name along with the program counter (pc), providing more context for debugging.
- **Threading and Synchronization Fixes:**
    - The `wait()` method in `java.lang.Object` was corrected to no longer wake up blocked threads directly.
    - The scheduler in `jvm.js` was updated to correctly transition `BLOCKED` threads to `runnable` when a lock is released.
    - The `monitorexit` instruction was corrected to no longer wake up blocked threads.
    - The `intValue()` method was implemented for `java.lang/Integer` to prevent a `Stack underflow` error.
- **New Test:** A new test was added for the `ProducerConsumer` example to verify that it runs to completion in a reasonable time and does not hang.

These changes together resolve a deadlock in the `ProducerConsumer` example and make the JVM more robust.

@@ -0,0 +1,340 @@
+// Package github provides a GitHub MCP server implementation for GitHub API operations.
+package github
+
+import (
+	"context"
+	"fmt"
+	"net/http"
+	"strconv"
+	"strings"
+	"time"
+
+	"github.com/google/go-github/v55/github"
+
+	"github.com/ondatra-ai/flow-test-go/pkg/errors"
+	"github.com/ondatra-ai/flow-test-go/pkg/types"
+)
+
+// Provider implements the GitHub MCP server provider.
+type Provider struct {
+	client *github.Client
+	token  string
+}
+
+// Config holds the configuration for the GitHub provider.
+type Config struct {
+	Token string `json:"token"`
+}
+
+// tokenTransport implements http.RoundTripper to add GitHub token authentication.
+type tokenTransport struct {
+	Token string
+	Base  http.RoundTripper
+}
+
+// RoundTrip implements http.RoundTripper interface to add Authorization header.
+func (t tokenTransport) RoundTrip(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, error) {
+	cloned := req.Clone(req.Context())
+	cloned.Header.Set("Authorization", "token "+t.Token)
+
+	response, err := t.base().RoundTrip(cloned)
+	if err != nil {
+		return nil, fmt.Errorf("GitHub API request failed: %w", err)
+	}
+
+	return response, nil
+}
+
+// base returns the base transport, defaulting to http.DefaultTransport.
+func (t tokenTransport) base() http.RoundTripper {
+	if t.Base != nil {
+		return t.Base
+	}
+
+	return http.DefaultTransport
+}
+
+// New creates a new GitHub provider with the given token.
+func New(token string) (*Provider, error) {
+	if token == "" {
+		return nil, &types.ExecutionError{
+			Code:        "GITHUB_TOKEN_REQUIRED",
+			Message:     "GitHub token is required",
+			Details:     nil,
+			Recoverable: false,
+			Timestamp:   time.Now(),
+			StackTrace:  "",
+		}
+	}
+
+	// Create HTTP client with token authentication
+	httpClient := &http.Client{
+		Transport:     tokenTransport{Token: token, Base: nil},
+		CheckRedirect: nil,

pull_request.title: [Issue #49] User Story 2.3: GitHub MCP Server ‚Äî github_get_issue (Template-Conformant)
pull_request.body:
- Implement in-process github MCP provider
- Expose github_get_issue tool constrained to GitHub.com
- Add token authentication with proper redaction
- Classify API errors (401/403 ‚Üí fatal, 429 ‚Üí retryable)
- Add unit and e2e tests
- Add static error definitions for GitHub provider to fix golangci-lint err113 violations
- Move environment variable resolution to shared ResolveEnvVar function in types package
- Update GitHub provider to use wrapped static errors instead of dynamic errors
- Add environment variable resolution to MCP server configuration
- Update GitHub provider tests to match new error message format
- Improve GitHub integration test to verify actual tool execution flow

**Related Issue**: #49: GitHub Reader Step Implementation

Implements GitHub MCP provider exposing github_get_issue tool with proper error handling, linting compliance, and comprehensive testing. The provider includes token authentication, error classification, and environment variable resolution for secure configuration management.

## Acceptance Criteria

[‚úì] Provider registers github_get_issue tool
[‚úì] Only api.github.com domain accepted
[‚úì] Success: Returns { title, body, state, labels } in Result and ContextWrites
[‚úì] Errors: Classified and written to ContextWrites.last_error
[‚úì] Tokens redacted from logs
[‚úì] Unit tests pass
[‚úì] All linting issues resolved with static error definitions
[‚úì] Environment variable resolution implemented
[ ] E2E tests pass with real GitHub API (requires .env.e2e with GITHUB_TOKEN)

## Implementation Details

- Created internal/github/provider.go with GitHub REST v3 client
- Added comprehensive parameter validation and error classification
- Implemented custom token transport for authentication
- Registered provider in MCP registry
- Added static error definitions to resolve golangci-lint violations
- Moved environment variable resolution to shared types package
- Added unit tests covering all validation scenarios
- Added e2e test framework (passes tool discovery, execution requires credentials)


<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->
## Summary by CodeRabbit

* **New Features**
  * GitHub integration: new MCP provider and github_get_issue tool to fetch issue details (title, body, state, labels).
  * MCP server configs support environment-variable placeholders (e.g., {env.VAR}) resolved at runtime.

* **Refactor**
  * Centralized environment-variable resolution into a shared ResolveEnvVar utility.

* **Tests**
  * Added unit and end-to-end tests for GitHub provider, env-var resolution, and tool execution.

* **Chores**
  * Go toolchain and dependency updates; added GitHub client dependencies.
<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->

issue.title: Last_update whitelisting at https://iso-stats.cachyos.org
issue.body:
### Prerequisites

- [x] I use the current version of the lists.
- [x] Disabling these lists resolves the issue.
- [x] I do not utilize a dedicated block page (e.g. NextDNS or ControlD block page) or a block mode that returns a custom IP for blocked domains. In my environment, blocked domains return a zero/null IP, or result in status NXDOMAIN or REFUSED for DNS resolutions.

### Which device type do you use?

Desktop

### Other device

_No response_

### What is the operating system of the device?

Linux

### Other operating system

_No response_

### Which browser or app are you using?

Other

### Other browser or app

pacman

### Which AdBlocker or DNS cloud service do you use?

AdGuard

### Other AdBlocker or DNS cloud service

_No response_

### Where does the issue occur - on which website or in which app?

pacman updating (CachyOS/Archlinux)

### Which blocklist(s) caused the issue?

Multi NORMAL

### Which domain(s) need to be unblocked?

```yaml
https://iso-stats.cachyos.org/api/v2/last_update_notice
```

### Why should the domain(s) be unblocked?

CachyOS uses a way to inform their users about manual migration, important information, and other before the user gets the update.

When the user updates the system, a update notice gets fetched and shown to the user. The user needs to explicitly confirm this message to proceed updating. This is a mechanism to avoid users not following blog posts, social media and co.

The "main" domain got blacklisted, since we track the downloads of our users at https://iso-stats.cachyos.org - this is fully fine for due the telemetry.
The block of the complete domain resulted now several times into a users broken system, since they could not follow the guidelines, which we provide in https://iso-stats.cachyos.org/api/v2/last_update_notice .

We please you the explicitly whitelist this URL since it does currently more harm then anything for our users.

### Confirmation

- [x] I have verified that the domain(s) are blocked by these blocklists and that the issue is not caused by any other additional blocklists in use.
- [x] I have verified that the unblocking of the domain(s) has not been declined in any existing issue.
- [x] I have provided sufficient details to verify the need for unblocking the domain(s).
- [ ] I did not answer truthfully to any of the above checkboxes.

### Terms

- [x] I confirm that the request does not contain any sexually explicit material or private/sensitive information.

issue.title: There seems to be no way of getting all images for certain forms?
issue.body:
I apologize if this mentioned somewhere, I'm new to the the API. But I didn't see any clear answer to this in the docs or in existing issues. It seems like there's images for certain forms that are not exposed by the API directly. I namely noticed this with Deerling, but it almost certainly applies elsewhere

If you check https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon/deerling, the `sprites` field only has data for the default (spring) form. The Pokemon has 3 other forms however:

- https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon-form/10068 (summer)
- https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon-form/10069 (autumn)
- https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon-form/10070 (winter)

Each of these forms does have a `sprites` field as well, but they contain considerably less images than the `pokemon` endpoint provides, only providing the default sprites

Despite this, images for other platforms DO exist for these forms. Such as:

- https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/blob/master/sprites/pokemon/versions/generation-vi/x-y/585-summer.png
- https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/blob/master/sprites/pokemon/versions/generation-vi/x-y/585-autumn.png
- https://github.com/PokeAPI/sprites/blob/master/sprites/pokemon/versions/generation-vi/x-y/585-winter.png

But it seems like these images are not exposed by the API? The `pokemon-form` endpoints all point back to the same base form (spring), and none of the alternate forms seem to have dedicated `pokemon` entries

I suspect this issue applies to all Pokemon with multiple forms where the forms do not have dedicated `pokemon` entries, not just Deerling. I also noticed this same issue with Flabebe, as if has multiple forms and images for other platforms but seemingly no way to get the images from the API?
